OL,7,FWhen Saghar Khalid, an Afghan refugee
OL,8,Fwho fled Kabul two years ago, was
OL,9,Fgetting her hair cut in Liverpool one
OL,10,Fday, she was puzzled by what her
OL,11,Fhairdresser was asking her to do.
OL,13,F"I didn't understand what she was
OL,14,Fsaying because she had a very heavy
OL,15,Faccent," Ms Khalid recalled, bursting
OL,16,Finto a fit of giggles. With the help
OL,17,Fof some miming, she realised she was
OL,18,Fbeing told to stand up.
OL,3,C'Love the accent but hate cold
OL,4,Csandwiches': An Afghan refugee's
OL,5,Cjourney from Kabul to Liverpool
